events.1830: Settlement of Akmoly established as the seat of an okrug
events.1832: Akmoly granted town status and renamed Akmolinsk
events.1869: Akmolinsk becomes the center of newly established Akmolinsk Oblast
events.1950: Akmolinsk designated as the administrative and cultural center of the Virgin Lands Campaign and renamed Tselinograd
events.1997: Akmola made the capital of Kazakhstan
events.1998: Akmola renamed Astana, meaning 'capital city' in Kazakh
events.2019: Astana renamed Nur-Sultan in honor of Nursultan Nazarbayev
events.2022: Astana readopted as the city's name following a proposal by members of the Parliament of Kazakhstan
